{
  "doc_id": "57681",
  "text": "All self-report measures were completed as part of a standardized assessment protocol prior to intake. Following completion of the self-report instruments, subjects were interviewed with the SCIDV by a doctoral candidate in clinical psychology trained in the administration of the SCIDV. Inclusion criteria for the study were: (1) completion of the MMPI, and (2) the occurrence of at least one violent incident by the current partner. Total scores for the 49-item PK-scale were calculated; subjects were assigned to F'TSD-Positive (N = 48) and PTSD-Negative (N = 21) groups using the cutoff score of 2 19 recommended by [CITATION_1] . Group comparisons for categorical and continuous dependent variables were conducted using 2x2 chi-squares and one-tailed t-tests, respectively.",
